														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1215878">
									

<p>No, no, those weren't actual questions asking for answers, mostly because answers would make it weaker. What I meant is, these are the things you leave out that I want to know, and I have only my imagination available to fill in the blanks. I'm envisioning 962 going absolutely nuts if a human approached closely, and every time I try to think of what that would entail, my mind comes up with something new.</p>
<p>These are exactly the types of questions that strengthen an SCP. I understand what it does, I understand why the Foundation contains it, and I understand (roughly) what it's trying to do. What I don't know is the why behind any of these, and that's a great question for me to be asking.</p>
<p>Just don't ruin it by actually answering!</p>

